definition: the straw that broke the camel’s back (idiom)/the final straw
pinyin: ya1 si3 luo4 tuo5 de5 zui4 hou4 yi1 gen1 dao4 cao3
containing_words.word: 压死骆驼的最后一根稻草

definition: the Last Supper (in the biblical Passion story)
the Last Supper (in the Christian Passion story)
He laughs best who laughs last.
pinyin: shei2 xiao4 dao4 zui4 hou4 , shei2 xiao4 de2 zui4 hao3
containing_words.word: 谁笑到最后，谁笑得最好

sentences.english: At last, the general equation for separation of high order definite err…
sentences.chinese: 最后给出了分离多阶确定性误差的通式。

sentences.english: Change that arrangement and you can dramatically alter the resulting organism.
sentences.chinese: 改变这个排列你就能完全改变最后的生物体。

sentences.english: At (long) last we found out what had really happened.
sentences.chinese: 最后，我们终于弄清了实际发生的情况。

sentences.english: The last chapter gives an indication of the state-of-the-art in an industrial environment.
sentences.chinese: 最后一章在一种工业环境里表示最新型。

sentences.english: And when finally I put it down, my mind was totally refreshed.
sentences.chinese: 最后放下书来时，我倦意全消，身心为之一爽。

sentences.english: The last stage of the birth process involves the delivery of the placenta, which is now called the afterbirth.
sentences.chinese: 分娩的最后一个阶段是胎盘的出来。

sentences.english: Plus, although she's a vampire, she doesn't go around killing innocent humans.
sentences.chinese: 最后，尽管她是一名吸血鬼，她并没有滥杀无辜人类。

sentences.english: The shipping charges for returning samples will be added to your final invoice.
sentences.chinese: 运费为返回的样品将增加来您最后的发货票。

sentences.english: Four measures of anti-interference are introduced briefly.
sentences.chinese: 最后简单介绍了四种抗干扰措施。

sentences.english: Keyes, however, was on foot at the back of the parade.
sentences.chinese: 然而，凯斯走在游行队伍的最后面。

sentences.english: Finally, some advice was put forward on the research directions of FOD tolerance design technology in China.
sentences.chinese: 最后对我国外物损伤容限设计的研究方向提出了建议。

sentences.english: The last lane is Method, indicating where the lock contends.
sentences.chinese: 最后一列是方法，表明锁竞争是在什么位置发生的。

sentences.english: Finally, we give the prospect of VDSL.
sentences.chinese: 最后，展望了VDSL的发展前景。

sentences.english: In a funny way, it was the last day at Highbury.
sentences.chinese: 在海布里的最后一天，这多少让人觉得有点不舒服。

sentences.english: Finally, an application example of excavator design was proposed to illuminate the reconstruction of traditional functions.
sentences.chinese: 最后，以挖掘机设计目标为例，进行了函数改造说明。

sentences.english: The motion that the remark of the last speaker be expunged from the record.
sentences.chinese: 该提议要求把最后一个发言的人的讲话从记录上除掉。

definition: (completed action marker)/(modal particle indicating change of state, situation now)/(modal particle intensifying preceding clause)
to finish/to achieve/variant of 瞭|了[liao3]/to understand clearly
again/once more/re-/second/another/then (after sth, and not until then)/no matter how ... (followed by an adjective or verb, and then (usually) 也[ye3] or 都[dou1] for emphasis)
of/~'s (possessive particle)/(used after an attribute)/(used to form a nominal expression)/(used at the end of a declarative sentence for emphasis)
outcome/result/conclusion/in the end/as a result/to kill/to dispatch
only/merely/no more than/but/however/anyway (to get back to a previous topic)/cannot be more (after adjectival)
